		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30008381">Well, genres are pretty silly little things and separating anime this way is riddled with imperfections, but I guess they work okay-ish as conversational shortcuts. But really, slice of life is just like any other genre. It can work as it's own thing or just another element in a larger genre recipe. I think this "vagueness" stems from that. It's this weird compulsion to categorize anime into perfect little genre titles. I mean, Pokemon can be magical realism with elements of slice of life just fine. <br />
<br />
So I wouldn't really say it's vague, it just goes against some bizarre, human (or maybe just nerdy) need to categorize things perfectly. Providing one isn't in a hurry, I think it's best to leave silly genre shit at the door and do your best to explain the anime in your own words.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><div style="text-align: right;"><!--link--><a href="http://drillmilkyholmes.wordpress.com/" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.imgur.com/7ALjX4f.png" /></a></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
