		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30028843">Slice-of-life is a perfectly good genre label. It's just that a lot of anime has elements of it. For example, many anime have romantic elements, but only some of them are labeled romance. The same goes with other big genres like drama (an anime wouldn't have a story if it weren't dramatic at all!) So some anime that focus completely on slice-of-life are labeled slice-of-life, but there are always many anime out there that include people simply wasting time and having fun without the slice-of-life label. How else is one going to fill up 12 or even 24 episodes?</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/animelist/einonymous&amp;sclick=1"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://myanimelist.net/signature/einonymous.png" /></a> </div></td>
